  <Name>k__BackingField: 1 Peter
  fancyName: 
  nickname: 1pe
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: d0ec49142d5c7c24fb05ee739840cab0, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Greeting'
      title: Greeting
      number: 1
      content: ' Peter, an apostle of Jesus Christ, to the chosen who are residing
        temporarily in the dispersion in Pontus, Galatia, Cappadocia, Asia, and Bithynia, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: A New Birth to a Living Hope'
      title: A New Birth to a Living Hope
      number: 2
      content: 'according to the foreknowledge of God the Father, by the sanctification
        of the Spirit, for obedience and for sprinkling with the blood of Jesus Christ.
        May grace and peace be multiplied to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Blessed be the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, who according
        to his great mercy has caused us to be born again to a living hope through
        the resurrection of Jesus Christ from the dead, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'into an inheritance imperishable and undefiled and unfading, reserved
        in heaven for you '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'who are being protected by the power of God through faith for a salvation
        ready to be revealed in the last time, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'in which you rejoice greatly, although now for a short time, if necessary,
        you are distressed by various trials, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'so that the genuineness of your faith, more valuable than gold that
        is passing away, but is tested by fire, may be found to result in praise
        and glory and honor at the revelation of Jesus Christ, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'whom, although you have not seen, you love; in whom now you believe,
        although you do not see him, and you rejoice greatly with joy inexpressible
        and full of glory, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'obtaining the goal of your faith, the salvation of your souls. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Concerning this salvation, the prophets who prophesied about the
        grace meant for you sought and made careful inquiry, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'investigating for what person or which time the Spirit of Christ
        in them was indicating when he testified beforehand to the sufferings with
        reference to Christ and the glories after these things, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Be Holy in All Your Conduct'
      title: Be Holy in All Your Conduct
      number: 12
      content: 'to whom it was revealed that they were serving not themselves but
        you with reference to the same things which now have been announced to you
        through those who proclaimed the gospel to you by the Holy Spirit sent from
        heaven, things into which angels desire to look. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Therefore, when you have prepared your minds for action by being
        self-controlled, put your hope completely in the grace that will be brought
        to you at the revelation of Jesus Christ. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'As obedient children, do not be conformed to the former desires you
        used to conform to in your ignorance, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'but as the one who called you is holy, you yourselves be holy in
        all your conduct, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "for it is written, \u201CYou will be holy, because I am holy.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And if you call on him as Father who judges impartially according
        to each one\u2019s work, conduct yourselves with fear during the time of
        your temporary residence, "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'because you know that you were redeemed from your futile way of life
        inherited from your ancestors not with perishable things like silver or gold, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'but with the precious blood of Christ, like that of an unblemished
        and spotless lamb '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'who was foreknown before the foundation of the world, but has been
        revealed in these last times for you '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'who through him are believing in God, who raised him from the dead
        and gave him glory, so that your faith and hope are in God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Having purified your souls by your obedience to the truth for sincere
        brotherly love, love one another fervently from the heart,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'because you have been born again, not from perishable seed but imperishable,
        through the living and enduring word of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "For \u201Call flesh is like grass, and all its glory like the flower
        of the grass. The grass withers and the flower falls off, "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "but the word of the Lord endures forever.\u201D  And this is the
        word that has been proclaimed to you. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Chosen as Living Stones'
      title: Chosen as Living Stones
      number: 1
      content: ' Therefore, ridding yourselves of all malice and all deceit and hypocrisy
        and envy and all slander, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'like newborn infants long for the unadulterated spiritual milk, so
        that by it you may grow up to salvation, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'if you have tasted that the Lord is kind,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'to whom you are drawing near, a living stone rejected by men but
        chosen and precious in the sight of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And you yourselves, as living stones, are being built up as a spiritual
        house for a holy priesthood, to offer up spiritual sacrifices acceptable
        to God through Jesus Christ. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For it stands in scripture, \u201CBehold, I am laying in Zion a stone,
        a chosen and precious cornerstone, and the one who believes in him will never
        be put to shame.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Therefore the honor is for you who believe, but for those who refuse
        to believe, \u201CThe stone that the builders rejected, this one has become
        the cornerstone,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "and \u201CA stone of stumbling and a rock of offense,\u201D  who
        stumble because they disobey the word to which also they were consigned. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But you are a chosen race, a royal priesthood, a holy nation, a people
        for God\u2019s possession, so that you may proclaim the virtues of the one
        who called you out of darkness into his marvelous light, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'who once were not a people, but now are the people of God, the ones
        who were not shown mercy, but now are shown mercy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Dear friends, I urge you as foreigners and temporary residents to
        abstain from fleshly desires which wage war against your soul, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Submission to Established Authority'
      title: Submission to Established Authority
      number: 12
      content: 'maintaining your good conduct among the Gentiles, so that in the
        things in which they slander you as evildoers, by seeing your good deeds
        they may glorify God on the day of visitation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Subject yourselves to every human authority for the sake of the Lord,
        whether to a king as having supreme authority, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'or to governors as those sent out by him for the punishment of those
        who do evil and the praise of those who do good. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For the will of God is as follows: by doing good to silence the ignorance
        of foolish people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Live as free persons, and not using your freedom as a covering for
        evil, but as slaves of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Honor all people, love the community of believers, fear God, honor
        the king.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Domestic slaves, be subject to your masters with all respect, not
        only to those who are good and gentle, but also to those who are unjust. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For this finds favor, if because of consciousness of God someone
        endures sorrows while suffering unjustly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'For what credit is it if, when you sin and are beaten for it, you
        endure? But if you endure when you do good and suffer for it, this finds
        favor with God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For to this you were called, because Christ also suffered for you,
        leaving you an example, so that you should follow in his footsteps, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'who did not commit sin, nor was deceit found in his mouth,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'who when he was reviled, did not revile in return; when suffering,
        he did not threaten, but entrusted himself to the one who judges justly, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'who himself bore our sins in his body on the tree, so that we may
        die to sins and live to righteousness, by whose wounds you were healed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'For you were going astray like sheep, but you have turned back now
        to the shepherd and guardian of your souls. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Wives and Husbands'
      title: Wives and Husbands
      number: 1
      content: ' In the same way, wives, be subject to your own husbands, so that
        even if some are disobedient to the word, they may be won over without a
        word by the conduct of their wives, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'when they see your respectful, pure conduct. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Let your adornment not be the external kind, braiding hair and putting
        on gold jewelry or putting on fine clothing, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'but the hidden person of the heart, with the imperishable quality
        of a gentle and quiet spirit, which is highly valuable in the sight of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For in the same way formerly the holy women also, who hoped in God,
        used to adorn themselves by being subject to their own husbands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'like Sarah obeyed Abraham, calling him lord, whose children you have
        become when you do good and are not frightened with respect to any terror. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Called to Inherit a Blessing'
      title: Called to Inherit a Blessing
      number: 7
      content: 'Husbands, in the same way live with your wives knowledgeably, as
        with the weaker female vessel, showing them honor as fellow heirs also of
        the grace of life, so that your prayers will not be hindered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And finally, all of you be harmonious, sympathetic, showing mutual
        affection, compassionate, humble, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'not repaying evil for evil or insult for insult, but on the other
        hand blessing others, because for this reason you were called, so that you
        could inherit a blessing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For \u201CThe one who wants to love life and see good days must keep
        his tongue from evil and his lips must not speak deceit. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And he must turn away from evil and do good; he must seek peace and
        pursue it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Suffer for Doing What is Good'
      title: Suffer for Doing What is Good
      number: 12
      content: 'For the eyes of the Lord are on the righteous, and his ears are open
        to their prayer. But the face of the Lord is against those who do evil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And who is the one who will harm you if you are a zealous adherent
        for what is good? '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But even if you might suffer for the sake of righteousness, you are
        blessed. And do not be afraid of their intimidation or be disturbed,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'but set Christ apart as Lord in your hearts, always ready to make
        a defense to anyone who asks you for an accounting concerning the hope that
        is in you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But do so with courtesy and respect, having a good conscience, so
        that in the things in which you are slandered, the ones who malign your good
        conduct in Christ may be put to shame. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For it is better to suffer for doing good, if God wills it, than
        for doing evil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For Christ also suffered once for sins, the just for the unjust,
        in order that he could bring you to God, being put to death in the flesh,
        but made alive in the spirit, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'in which also he went and proclaimed to the spirits in prison, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "who were formerly disobedient, when the patience of God waited in
        the days of Noah, while an ark was being constructed, in which a few\u2014that
        is, eight souls\u2014were rescued through water. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And also, corresponding to this, baptism now saves you, not the removal
        of dirt from the flesh, but an appeal to God for a good conscience through
        the resurrection of Jesus Christ, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'who is at the right hand of God, having gone into heaven, with angels
        and authorities and powers having been subjected to him. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Time for Behaving Like the Gentiles is Past'
      title: The Time for Behaving Like the Gentiles is Past
      number: 1
      content: ' Therefore, because Christ suffered in the flesh, you also equip
        yourselves with the same way of thinking, because the one who has suffered
        in the flesh has ceased from sin, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'in order to live the remaining time in the flesh no longer for human
        desires, but for the will of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For the time that has passed was sufficient to do what the Gentiles
        desire to do, having lived in licentiousness, evil desires, drunkenness,
        carousing, drinking parties, and wanton idolatries, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'with respect to which they are surprised when you do not run with
        them into the same flood of dissipation, and so they revile you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They will give an account to the one who is ready to judge the living
        and the dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Serving to the Glory of God'
      title: Serving to the Glory of God
      number: 6
      content: "Because for this reason also the gospel was preached to those who
        are dead, so that they were judged by human standards in the flesh, but they
        may live in the spirit by God\u2019s standards. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now the end of all things draws near. Therefore be self-controlled
        and sober-minded for your prayers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Above all, keep your love for one another constant, because love
        covers a large number of sins. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Be hospitable to one another without complaining. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Just as each one has received a gift, use it for serving one another,
        as good stewards of the varied grace of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Sharing the Sufferings of Christ'
      title: Sharing the Sufferings of Christ
      number: 11
      content: 'If anyone speaks, let it be as the oracles of God; if anyone serves,
        let it be as by the strength that God provides, so that in all things God
        will be glorified through Jesus Christ, to whom is the glory and the power
        forever and ever. Amen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Dear friends, do not be surprised at the fiery ordeal among you,
        when it takes place to test you, as if something strange were happening to
        you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But to the degree that you share in the sufferings of Christ, rejoice,
        so that also at the revelation of his glory you may rejoice and be glad. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'If you are reviled on account of the name of Christ, you are blessed,
        because the Spirit of glory and of God rests on you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'By all means do not let anyone of you suffer as a murderer or a thief
        or an evildoer or as a meddler. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But if someone suffers as a Christian, he must not be ashamed, but
        must glorify God with this name. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For it is the time for the judgment to begin out from the household
        of God. But if it begins out from us first, what will be the outcome for
        those who are disobedient to the gospel of God? '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And if the righteous are saved with difficulty, what will become
        of the ungodly and the sinner?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So then also those who suffer according to the will of God must entrust
        their souls to a faithful Creator in doing good. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Leadership and Humility'
      title: Leadership and Humility
      number: 1
      content: ' Therefore I, your fellow elder and a witness of the sufferings of
        Christ, and also a sharer of the glory that is going to be revealed, exhort
        the elders among you: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'shepherd the flock of God among you, exercising oversight not by
        compulsion but willingly, in accordance with God, and not greedily but eagerly, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and not as lording it over those under your care, but being examples
        for the flock. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And when the chief Shepherd appears, you will receive the unfading
        crown of glory. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'In the same way, younger men, be subject to the elders, and all of
        you clothe yourselves with humility toward one another, because God opposes
        the proud, but gives grace to the humble. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Humble yourselves therefore under the mighty hand of God, so that
        he may exalt you at the right time, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'casting all your cares on him, because he cares for you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Be sober; be on the alert. Your adversary the devil walks around
        like a roaring lion, looking for someone to devour. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Resist him, steadfast in your faith, because you know the same kinds
        of sufferings are being accomplished by your community of believers in the
        world. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And the God of all grace, who called you to his eternal glory in
        Christ, after you have suffered for a short time, will himself restore, confirm,
        strengthen, and establish you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Conclusion and Final Greetings'
      title: Conclusion and Final Greetings
      number: 11
      content: 'To him be the power forever and ever. Amen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Through Silvanus, the faithful brother (as I consider him), I have
        written to you briefly to encourage you and to attest that this is the true
        grace of God. Stand firm in it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'She who is in Babylon, chosen the same as you, greets you, and so
        does my son Mark. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Greet one another with a loving kiss. Peace to all of you who are
        in Christ. '
      comments: []
